    • Constructor Detail

      • LazyProcessResourceImpl

        public LazyProcessResourceImpl(String metacardId,
                               Supplier<Resource> resourceSupplier)
        Creates a ProcessResource with a Supplier used to load the Resource. The resource will not be loaded until the first time one of the following fields is accessed: inputStream mimeType name
        Parameters:
        metacardId - schema specific part of URI, throws IllegalArgumentException if empty or null
        resourceSupplier - a Supplier used to load the resource
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the input provided is not valid

        public String getQualifier()
        An optional field to provide additional information about a ProcessResource, that if present, indicates that this ProcessResource is derived from another Resource. The parent content of this ProcessResource is this ProcessResource's URI without the qualifier.

        This value should not require the resources to be loaded.
